questionRound.0.question.9.answer: I always look at the payoff of whichever color goes last first.  Based on that  I assume that person will select the options giving a higher rate of payoff.  Using this person's decision  I look at other player's payoffs in reverse chronological order to determine the most likely actions these people will take.  Taking these decisions into account  I will select whichever outcome gives me higher earnings.  I never took into account the decisions of those who came before me unless i was the last person to select an outcome.
work backwards; last player (orange in this case)  will tend to choose XO because XO will always yield more than YO.

If I wasn't first  I would look at what the last person would choose (which should be decided by what the first person chose)  and would work my way back to myself that way. If I was first  I would see what others would choose  working my way forward from the last person  based on if I chose X and if I chose Y and decided on the one that had a better outcome for me (all the time assuming that each person would chose what is best for them)

When I wasn't the first person in the sequence I just looked at what other people chose and used their answers to determine what would yield the higher payout for me.  |  | When I was the first person in the sequence I tried both option  X and Y and then followed each of those through to see what it would eventually cause the second person in the sequence to do (because the second person directly impacts my payout). Then I compared these two payouts and went with the option that yielded the higher one.

In order to maximize payoff  players must think in reverse and figure out what the person ahead of them will choose. | If I choose XR  Orange will choose XO  and Blue will choose YB  and Green will choose XG  and when Green choose XG  I end up with a payoff of 8. | If I choose YR  Orange will choose XO  and Blue will still choose YB  and Green will still choose XG. However  if I chose YR  and Green chooses XG  I get a payoff of 28. |

The last table of the player is structured in a way that it is easy to tell what the last player would choose. Assuming that everyone wants to get the highest points  it is very predictable. Sometimes people mess up and it becomes a tragedy  but as the game goes on  other players start getting better and better so we no longer mess up.

Worked bakwards  determining which selection the last player would make based on the first player's choice.  If I had the firt turn  I would simulate the scenario that would play out with both of my options.

If the person who decided my column had not gone yet  I looked at which color would decide the column that I would get  then I looked at what they would choose based if they were rational based on who decided their column  etc. etc. If the person who decided my column had already gone I simply picked which row would give me the highest value in that column.  | The row that had the highest possible number also had a number lower than the higher number in the other row  and when going first I realized that even if I picked the row with the highest possibility  based on what other people's decisions would probably be I would end up getting the lowest possibility which was also in that row. Therefore  when I was first I picked the row not necessarily with the highest number  but with option that would get me the highest value based on what other people would probably do. This usually ended up getting me the second highest value.

For Red  I just figured that with XR  it didn't matter which one I got  it would still be higher than either from YR. Then looking at what Red chose  I could predict Orange because Orange needs Red to figure out how to get the most points. In this case  orange would pick XO.  Blue can use Red to guess orange and then use orange to pick which one would give the most points. Since orange picked XO because Red picked XR  the logical guess would be YB. Then green could go through this whole line of assumptions and pick XG to get the most points from Blue's YB. I don't know if this is making any sense...I messed up a few times.

I will try to predict other players decisions by finding out the dominating strategry  which can be typically found in the fourth player. Ideally  everyone will make a rational decision that will maxinize the total earning of our group. However  there were few games where others didn't follow the rules.
Following t6o see what the group before me chose.
